### **Current Weather (as of June 2024)**  
- **Summer (June-August):** Typically mild to warm, with average highs of **18–23°C (64–73°F)**. However, heatwaves can push temperatures above **30°C (86°F)**.  
- **Rainfall:** Showers are possible at any time, even in summer, though heavy downpours are less frequent than in winter.  

### **General Seasonal Trends**  
- **Spring (March-May):** Cool to mild, with increasing sunshine. Average highs: **11–18°C (52–64°F)**.  
- **Autumn (September-November):** Gradually cooling, often wet and windy. Average highs: **11–20°C (52–68°F)**.  
- **Winter (December-February):** Chilly but rarely extreme, with highs around **7–9°C (45–48°F)**. Frost and occasional snow are possible.  

### **Key Features of London Weather**  
✔ **Unpredictable** – Rain can happen any day, so carrying an umbrella is wise.  
✔ **Moderate extremes** – Rarely too hot or too cold, but humidity can make it feel different.  
✔ **Drizzle & overcast skies** – Common, especially in autumn/winter.  

For the **most up-to-date forecast**, check sources like:  
- [BBC Weather](https://www.bbc.co.uk/weather)  
- [Met Office](https://www.metoffice.gov.uk/)
